pr_body:
@choffmeister,
issue: 
<img width="350" alt="screen shot 2017-10-09 at 2 34 54 pm" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9293338/31336333-0fc167d2-acff-11e7-908b-29c4a6464baf.png">

How to represent this bug:
```css
font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
font-weight: 300;
```

@mbabineau I was preparing for another release and was about to edit the changelog and though "this should be automated".

Mind if we start using https://github.com/skywinder/github-changelog-generator to automake the changelog?

The main thing I was *actually* looking for was those `compare` links that let you show the commits between releases

Re-execing is now not needed for most of Ganga and this was breaking the logging while running tests.

This change allows all logging messages to be correctly captured by the test framework.

@rob-c I believe this addresses the complaint you had last week about logging within tests.

Closes #103 and graphql-python/graphene#638

`graphql-js` handles this case as expected and now using the python port for work I was surprised to see the default resolver lacked this feature. Using dict literals in resolvers is much more convenient than creating a namedtuple for everything.

@syrusakbary please consider merging this, from the linked issues it seems I'm not alone in this feeling.
